text:
Northern Boulevard, east from 113th Street, showing the Boulevard being widened to accomodate travelers to the New York World's Fair of 1939-40. Note the Flushing dumps on the right. View 2 shows the same area a year later. View 3 is on the north side of the Boulevard, at 114th Street. In the background is Flushing Bay and the village of Flushing.

P. L. Sperr

View 1: October 4, 1935
Views 2,3: October 21, 1936
